<b>Posted On:</b> 6:50 p.m. 10/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: The Only Way to do PVP!!!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=660" TARGET=_self>The Only Way to do PVP!!!</A> (Platinum)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>The PvP switch was implemented so jerks couldn't kill people that didn't want to participate in PvP. Your enjoyment is no more important than anyone elses. And oddly enough, some people don't enjoy being jumped by 6 little fools. The system you propose does nothing to stop this. Alignment? People will be killing everyone they see just so they can say they are the most evil. And so what if they become outcasts in every city, they're sure to have multiple characters to buy things for them.

<P>If they could balance the levels so that killing someone 1 level above you wasn't damn near impossible, the current system will be great.
<P>The only thing wrong with the PvP switch is that it needs to exist.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
